I love the simplicity of Linux and Bash. Probably why I prefer it over the unneccesary complexities of powershell. Nonetheless I am using it to familiarize myself with the commands.
I was using Git Bash that ships with git for Windows, until I discovered the power of Windows Terminal1, an exceptional terminal emulator that enhanced my &ldquo;Windows experience.&rdquo;
I like the seamless integration between different shells and its customizability, in contrast to the uninspiring blue powershell.

in this blog, i will share a list of no-nonense scripts for mpv.
if you are not using mpv, and using something else &ndash; here are few reasons why you must consider it:
lightweight customizable with scripting support relatively easy to setup and use faster than vlc Scripts mpv chapters mpv thumbnails script 1. mpv chapters1 Display chapters and allow you to jump to them with a mouse click. as easy as saving the file in your scripts/ folder.
